    <!-- Chosen Palette: Corporate Calm -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page dashboard with a top navigation bar for smooth scrolling to thematic sections. The core design is a side-by-side comparison of Missouri and California for each topic, which is the most intuitive way to present this comparative data. A primary toggle allows users to filter the view to a single state, simplifying the interface for focused research. This structure was chosen to directly answer the user's comparative query, making it easy to see differences at a glance while allowing for deeper dives into specific topics or states. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Regulatory Info -> Goal: Compare Complexity -> Viz: Key-value list in cards -> Interaction: State filter toggle -> Justification: Textual comparison is best for nuanced regulatory details. Bond Requirements -> Goal: Compare Amounts -> Viz: Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover tooltips -> Justification: Directly visualizes the significant difference in capital requirements. Revenue Structure -> Goal: Compare Income Streams -> Viz: Donut Charts (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover tooltips -> Justification: Clearly shows the proportional differences in revenue sources. Staffing -> Goal: Compare Team Composition -> Viz: Tabular card format -> Interaction: State filter toggle -> Justification: Best for comparing roles and required qualifications. Digitization -> Goal: Compare Tech Adoption -> Viz: Radar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover tooltips -> Justification: Provides a multi-dimensional view of technological advancement across different facets of the industry. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
